abstract="{Summary: When a flow, discontinuous across a switching surface,
    points `inward' so one cannot leave, it induces a unique flow within the
    surface, called the sliding mode. When several such surfaces intersect, the
    authors seek a flow within the intersection, but some difficulties arise.
